      "rationale": "All three FEA codes (FDA in-house, Ansys 2022 R1, DePuy Synthes internal) operate under documented QMS procedures including version control, regression testing, and release qualification. Achieved level 3 exceeds required level 2 for this model risk tier."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Each code in the ensemble has been verified against published benchmark problems relevant to structural mechanics of metallic implants. Patch tests and manufactured-solution benchmarks confirm correct implementation of constitutive models and contact algorithms."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Mesh convergence study performed across three refinement levels for the pedicle screw shank and rod junction. Global energy norm and local peak stress at the screw-rod interface converge within 3% between the two finest meshes, satisfying the required discretization error criterion."
    },
    {
