      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Quantities of interest (construct stiffness, load at 5 mm displacement) are the primary regulatory endpoints for ASTM F1717 submissions and directly support the intended use claim of predicting mechanical performance of non-cannulated pedicle screw constructs."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Validation activities replicate the ASTM F1717 test protocol in geometry, loading, and boundary conditions. The non-cannulated 7.5 mm screw geometry tested matches the device geometry described in the intended use claim for lumbar spinal fixation. Validation scenario is judged highly relevant to the COU as characterised in the Claim and Requirement documentation."
